main event: Border guards in Iran reported observing an unidentified flying object on February 17, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed on the ground and was described as being shaped like a saucer or disc.
The report indicates that the observers were border guards, suggesting it was an official military or government observation.
The report states that there were no photographs taken of the object.
The duration and speed of the object were not reported, but it was possibly a rocket or missile.
The conclusion of the report was that there was insufficient data to evaluate the observation.
sighted object: saucer or disc-shaped unidentified flying object
